<IN>
MEDICAL SUPPLIES (MDS)
</IN>
<GV>
FOOD AND DRUG ADMINISTRATION (FDA)
</GV>
<LP>
   SUNNYVALE, Calif. -- Sunrise Technologies Inc. said it
received permission from the Food and Drug Administration to
market its dental laser device dLase 300 for soft tissue
surgery in the mouth.
   According to the American Dental Association, about 1.5
million people in the U.S. have such surgery for gum disease,
Sunrise said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company is also developing lasers for other dental and
eye applications.
</TEXT>
