<LP>
   PARIS -- The Franco-British heavy engineering group GEC
Alsthom announced yesterday that its Ruston Gas Turbines Co.
unit has won about 400 million francs ($72.7 million) of new
orders from offshore oil sites in the North Sea.
   GEC Alsthom said that the orders cover three gas-powered
turbines of 33 megawatts each for the Scott platform operated
by New York-based Amerada Hess Corp. as well as three
turbine-powered compressor groups for the East Brae platform
operated by Marathon Oil UK Ltd. a unit of Pittsburgh-based
USX Corp.
</LP>
