   MERRILL LYNCH &amp; Co. (New York) -- Merrill Lynch Capital
Markets, a unit, named John F. Lyness managing director, debt
trading and sales in London. Mr. Lyness formerly was head of
mortgage trading and finance at Morgan Stanley &amp; Co. Mr.
Lyness succeeds Donald A. Wright, who was named president of
Merrill Lynch Canada in Toronto. Merrill's former head of
Canadian operations, Michael Sanderson, resigned to become
president and chief executive officer of Instinet Corp., the
equities trading unit of Reuters Hold ings PLC, London.
</LP>
