   Herbert D. Ihle, former controller of Pillsbury Co., was
named senior vice president, finance, a new position.
   Richard B. Hirst, former general counsel at Texas Air
Corp.'s Continental Airlines unit, was named Northwest's
general counsel. He succeeds Timothy R. Thorton, who was
named to the new position of executive vice president, labor
relations.
   Two other current Northwest executives were promoted.
Robert L. Fornaro, vice president, marketing planning, was
named senior vice president in the same area. R. Terrence
Rendleman, vice president for maintenance and engineering,
was named senior vice president, technical operations.
