</HL>
<DATE>
05/11/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A9A
</SO>
<CO>
   FREST
</CO>
<IN>
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
</IN>
<LP>
   MANILA, the Philippines -- Total imports in the
Philippines reached $2.44 billion from Jan. 1 to April 7 of
this year, up 11.9%, from $2.18 billion a year ago, the
Central Bank of the Philippines said.
   Oil imports amounted to $400.3 million, or 20.1% higher
than $333.2 million a year earlier. Oil receipts in the
three-month period are equivalent to 16.4% of total imports.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The country imported $2.04 billion of non-oil merchandise,
which is 10.2% more than $1.85 billion in the same period
last year.
