the buy-back strategy is common among companies in which
Warren E. Buffett is a major investor. Mr. Buffett, chairman
of Berkshire Hathaway Inc., controls 16.5% of Washington
Post's Class B stock, which are nonvoting shares. Class A
shares are 100% controlled by the family of Katharine Graham,
Washington Post chairman.
   The media company publishes the Washington Post newspaper
and Newsweek magazine.
