quarter. But Wednesday, Volkswagen Chairman Carl H. Hahn said
that in the first four months, Audi unit sales had risen 14%,
suggesting sales jumped sharply in April.
   Sales in the U.S. had been hurt in recent years by
since-discredited allegations that Audi cars had spontaneous
acceleration problems. Signs that Audi's U.S. sales had
turned the corner emerged in 1989.
