<HL>
   Business Brief -- Hershey Foods Corp.:
   Company to Sell 17% Stake
   In Sweden's AB Marabou
</HL>
<DATE>
05/11/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   HSY
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Hershey Foods Corp. signed a definitive agreement to sell
its 17% equity stake in AB Marabou, a Swedish confectionary
company, to Orkla Borregaard A.S. for more than $75 million.
Orkla is a Norwegian concern with interests in consumer
packaged goods, chemicals and communications.
   The Hershey, Pa., company said it expects the sale to
result in a one-time aftertax gain of more than $35 million,
or 39 cents a share. The gain from the sale, which requires
approval from the Swedish and Norwegian governments, will
most likely be applied to second-quarter results, said a
company spokesman.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Freia AS, a major Norwegian shareholder of Marabou, is in
the midst of a tender offer for those shares of Marabou it
doesn't own. The spokesman said Hershey decided not to tender
its shares because Orkla offered about $12 million more for
the food company's stake, which carries 20% of the voting
rights. "It's called maximizing shareholder value," he said.
</TEXT>
